{"type":"text","timestamp":1775902621911,"sessionID":"ses_283f50cecffeSn1ZLPg1jFwh0T","part":{"id":"prt_d7c0b7be30018pr0XmMINns7LF","messageID":"msg_d7c0b60e6001nJ3f0jJsot9G1F","sessionID":"ses_283f50cecffeSn1ZLPg1jFwh0T","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the format. The existing `python-sdk/design.md` is quite minimal compared to other design documents in the project. I need to enhance it with proper architecture diagrams, data flow descriptions, component interactions, error handling, and testing strategy sections.\n\nLet me write the comprehensive design.md:","time":{"start":1775902621909,"end":1775902621909}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775902781885,"sessionID":"ses_283f50cecffeSn1ZLPg1jFwh0T","part":{"id":"prt_d7c0b80d7001mSceAj1qiHz4AH","messageID":"msg_d7c0b60e6001nJ3f0jJsot9G1F","sessionID":"ses_283f50cecffeSn1ZLPg1jFwh0T","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md","content":"# AR-027 Design: AgentCube Python SDK — CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-027  \n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **Workload Manager API**: Control plane for session lifecycle management\n- **Router API**: Data plane for code execution and file operations\n- **Agent Runtime API**: For agent workload invocation\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         User Application (Python)                            │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐                 │\n│  │ CodeInterpreterClient   │    │  AgentRuntimeClient     │                 │\n│  │ ┌───────────────────┐   │    │ ┌───────────────────┐   │                 │\n│  │ │ Context Manager   │   │    │ │ Context Manager   │   │                 │\n│  │ │ Lifecycle Mgmt    │   │    │ │ Lifecycle Mgmt    │   │                 │\n│  │ └───────────────────┘   │    │ └───────────────────┘   │                 │\n│  └───────────┬─────────────┘    └───────────┬─────────────┘                 │\n│              │                              │                                │\n└──────────────┼──────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\n               │                              │\n               ▼                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         SDK Internal Layer                                   │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │   ControlPlaneClient        │    │       Data Plane Clients            │  │\n│  │  ┌───────────────────────┐  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │ Session Management    │  │    │  │ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient│  │  │\n│  │  │ · create_session()    │──┘    │  │ · execute_command()           │  │  │\n│  │  │ · delete_session()    │       │  │ · run_code()                  │  │  │\n│  │  └───────────────────────┘       │  │ · write_file()                │  │  │\n│  │  HTTP Session (requests)         │  │ · upload_file()               │  │  │\n│  │  · Connection pooling            │  │ · download_file()             │  │  │\n│  │  · Auth: Bearer token            │  │ · list_files()                │  │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────┘  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│                                        ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│                                        │ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient   │  │  │\n│                                        │ · bootstrap_session_id()      │  │  │\n│                                        │ · invoke()                    │  │  │\n│                                        └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n               │                              │\n               ▼                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         External Services                                    │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │   Workload Manager          │    │         Router                      │  │\n│  │  ┌───────────────────────┐  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │ POST /v1/code-        │  │    │  │ Code Interpreter Endpoints    │  │  │\n│  │  │         interpreter   │  │    │  │ · POST api/execute            │  │  │\n│  │  │ DELETE /v1/code-      │  │    │  │ · POST api/files              │  │  │\n│  │  │   interpreter/        │  │    │  │ · GET api/files/{path}        │  │  │\n│  │  │   sessions/{id}       │  │    │  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  │  └───────────────────────┘  │    │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  Authorization: Bearer      │    │  │ Agent Runtime Endpoints       │  │  │\n│  └─────────────────────────────┘    │  │ · GET /invocations/           │  │  │\n│                                     │  │ · POST /invocations/          │  │  │\n│                                     │  └───────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│                                     └─────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     CodeInterpreterClient Flow                               │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  User    │──▶│ __init__ │──▶│  router_ │──▶│ Control  │──▶│  Create  │  │\n│  │ Creates  │   │ Validate │   │  url     │   │  Plane   │   │  Session │  │\n│  │  Client  │   │  Config  │   │  check   │   │  Client  │   │   or     │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │  Reuse   │  │\n│                                                              └────┬─────┘  │\n│                                                                   │        │\n│                              ┌────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n│                              │                                             │\n│                              ▼                                             │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  stop()  │◀──│ __exit__ │◀──│  Context │◀──│ DataPlane│◀──│ _init_   │  │\n│  │  Cleanup │   │ Cleanup  │   │  Manager │   │  Client  │   │data_plane│  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n│       │                                                           │        │\n│       ▼                                                           ▼        │\n│  ┌──────────┐                                            ┌──────────────┐  │\n│  │  Close   │                                            │ Execute/Files│  │\n│  │  Session │                                            │ Operations   │  │\n│  └──────────┘                                            └──────────────┘  │\n│                                                                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      AgentRuntimeClient Flow                                 │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  User    │──▶│ __init__ │──▶│ router_  │──▶│ DataPlane│──▶│ Bootstrap│  │\n│  │ Creates  │   │ Validate │   │ url check│   │  Client  │   │ Session  │  │\n│  │  Client  │   │  Config  │   │          │   │          │   │   ID     │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n│                                                                   │        │\n│                              ┌────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n│                              │                                             │\n│                              ▼                                             │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  close() │◀──│ __exit__ │◀──│  Context │◀──│  invoke()│◀──│  User    │  │\n│  │  Cleanup │   │ Cleanup  │   │  Manager │   │ POST JSON│   │ Invokes  │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │ + Headers│   │  Agent   │  │\n│                                               └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n│                                                                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **CodeInterpreterClient** | High-level client for code interpreter sessions | Configuration params | Session management, code execution |\n| **AgentRuntimeClient** | High-level client for agent runtime invocation | Agent name, namespace, payload | Invocation response |\n| **ControlPlaneClient** | Workload Manager API client | Session parameters | Session ID, deletion status |\n| **CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient** | Router API client for code operations | Commands, files, paths | Execution results, file data |\n| **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** | Router API client for agent invocation | Payload, session ID | HTTP response |\n| **create_session** | HTTP session factory | Pool config | requests.Session with adapter |\n| **read_token_from_file** | Service account token reader | File path | Token string or empty |\n| **get_logger** | Logging utility | Name, level | Logger instance |\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\nsdk-python/\n├── pyproject.toml                          # Package configuration\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                         # Public exports\n│   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # CodeInterpreterClient\n│   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── exceptions.py                       # Exception hierarchy\n│   ├── clients/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Client re-exports\n│   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient\n│   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n│   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── __init__.py                     # Module marker\n│       ├── http.py                         # create_session\n│       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file\n│       └── log.py                          # get_logger\n├── examples/\n│   ├── basic_usage.py                      # CodeInterpreter example\n│   └── agent_runtime_usage.py              # AgentRuntime example\n├── scripts/\n│   └── e2e_picod_test.py                   # End-to-end test\n└── tests/\n    └── *.py                                # Unit tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### CodeInterpreterClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    \"\"\"High-level client for Code Interpreter session management and execution.\n    \n    Fields (set in __init__):\n        name: str                    # Session name (default: \"my-interpreter\")\n        namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n        ttl: int                     # Session TTL in seconds (default: 3600)\n        verbose: bool                # Enable verbose logging (default: False)\n        logger: logging.Logger       # Logger instance\n        cp_client: ControlPlaneClient  # Control plane client\n        router_url: str              # Router URL (required)\n        session_id: Optional[str]    # Session ID (created or provided)\n        dp_client: Optional[CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient]  # Data plane client\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Constructor Parameters:**\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `name` | `str` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | Name for the code interpreter session |\n| `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `ttl` | `int` | `3600` | Session TTL in seconds |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL (or env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`) |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL (or env `ROUTER_URL`, required) |\n| `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Auth token (or service account token file) |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Existing session ID to reuse |\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    \"\"\"High-level client for Agent Runtime invocation.\n    \n    Fields (set in __init__):\n        agent_name: str              # Agent name\n        namespace: str               # Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n        timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n        connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n        logger: logging.Logger       # Logger instance\n        router_url: str              # Router URL (from arg or ROUTER_URL env)\n        session_id: Optional[str]    # Session ID (bootstrapped or provided)\n        dp_client: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient  # Data plane client\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Constructor Parameters:**\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Name of the agent to invoke |\n| `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL (or env `ROUTER_URL`) |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Existing session ID to reuse |\n| `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Read timeout in seconds |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connect timeout in seconds |\n\n### ControlPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Control plane client for Workload Manager API.\n    \n    Fields:\n        base_url: str                # Workload Manager base URL\n        timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n        connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n        session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Data plane client for Code Interpreter operations.\n    \n    Fields:\n        session_id: str              # Session ID for header\n        base_url: str                # Data plane base URL\n        timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n        connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n        session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Data plane client for Agent Runtime invocation.\n    \n    Constants:\n        SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n    \n    Fields:\n        base_url: str                # Data plane base URL\n        timeout: int                 # Read timeout (default: 120)\n        connect_timeout: float       # Connect timeout (default: 5.0)\n        session: requests.Session    # HTTP session with pooling\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Control Plane (Workload Manager)\n\n#### Session Creation\n\n```\nPOST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\n```\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"ttl\": 3600,\n  \"metadata\": {}\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"abc-123-def\"\n}\n```\n\n**Headers:**\n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n- `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n\n**Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n\n#### Session Deletion\n\n```\nDELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Returns `True` on success (2xx)\n- Returns `True` on 404 (already deleted)\n- Returns `False` on other errors (logs warning)\n\n### Data Plane (Code Interpreter)\n\n#### Base URL Construction\n\n```python\nif base_url is not provided:\n    base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n    self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n#### Execute Command\n\n```\nPOST {base_url}api/execute\n```\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"command\": [\"python3\", \"script.py\"],\n  \"timeout\": \"60s\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"stdout\": \"output text\",\n  \"stderr\": \"error text\",\n  \"exit_code\": 0\n}\n```\n\n**Timeout Behavior:**\n- Read timeout: `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- Raises `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n\n#### Write File\n\n```\nPOST {base_url}api/files\n```\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"/workspace/script.py\",\n  \"content\": \"base64_encoded_content\",\n  \"mode\": \"0644\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Upload File (Multipart)\n\n```\nPOST {base_url}api/files\nContent-Type: multipart/form-data\n```\n\n**Form Data:**\n- `file`: Binary file content\n- `path`: Remote path\n- `mode`: File permissions (e.g., \"0644\")\n\n**Headers:**\n- `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (only header, no JSON Content-Type)\n\n#### Download File\n\n```\nGET {base_url}api/files/{clean_path}\n```\n\nWhere `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n\n**Response:** Binary file content (streamed)\n\n#### List Files\n\n```\nGET {base_url}api/files?path={path}\n```\n\n### Data Plane (Agent Runtime)\n\n#### Base URL Construction\n\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n#### Bootstrap Session ID\n\n```\nGET {base_url}\n```\n\n**Response Headers:**\n- `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (required)\n\n**Error:**\n- Raises `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` if header missing\n\n#### Invoke Agent\n\n```\nPOST {base_url}\n```\n\n**Headers:**\n- `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n**Request Body:** JSON payload (dict)\n\n**Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```\nAgentCubeError (base)\n├── CommandExecutionError\n├── SessionError\n└── DataPlaneError\n```\n\n### Exception Definitions\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when remote command returns non-zero exit code.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: Optional[str] = None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\n    \n    Defined for extension; core client modules primarily use ValueError\n    or requests exceptions for session-related errors.\n    \"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\n    \n    Defined for extension; core client modules may raise ValueError\n    or requests exceptions for data plane errors.\n    \"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Error Type | Message/Behavior |\n|----------|------------|------------------|\n| Router URL not provided | `ValueError` | \"Router URL must be provided\" |\n| Session creation fails | `ValueError` / logs | Missing `sessionId` in response |\n| Data plane init fails after session create | Warning log + cleanup | Deletes session, re-raises |\n| Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError` | Includes exit_code, stderr, command |\n| Missing session header | `ValueError` | \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n| Invoke without session | `ValueError` | \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\" |\n| Session not found (404) | Handled gracefully | Returns `True` from `delete_session` |\n\n### Context Manager Cleanup\n\n**CodeInterpreterClient:**\n```python\ndef __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Cleanup on context exit (success or exception).\"\"\"\n    self.stop()\n\ndef stop(self) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Stop the client: close data plane, delete session, close control plane.\"\"\"\n    # 1. Close data plane client\n    # 2. Delete control plane session (if session_id was created)\n    # 3. Close control plane HTTP session\n```\n\n**AgentRuntimeClient:**\n```python\ndef __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Cleanup on context exit.\"\"\"\n    self.close()\n\ndef close(self) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Resolution\n\n### No Centralized Configuration Class\n\nThe SDK uses distributed configuration resolution across components:\n\n| Component | Setting | Resolution Order |\n|-----------|---------|------------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` arg → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `auth_token` | `auth_token` arg → `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` file |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` | `router_url` arg → `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` | `router_url` arg → `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n\n### Default Timeouts\n\n| Component | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout |\n|-----------|-----------------|--------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `5.0` seconds | `120` seconds |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `5.0` seconds | `120` seconds |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `5.0` seconds | `120` seconds |\n\n### HTTP Connection Pool\n\n```python\ndefaults = {\n    \"pool_connections\": 10,\n    \"pool_maxsize\": 10,\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Levels\n\n| Level | Scope | Focus |\n|-------|-------|-------|\n| **Unit** | Individual classes/methods | Logic, error paths, edge cases |\n| **Integration** | Client + Mock Server | HTTP contract verification |\n| **E2E** | Full stack (optional) | Real service connectivity |\n\n### Unit Test Coverage\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient Tests\n\n```python\n# test_code_interpreter.py\nclass TestCodeInterpreterClient:\n    def test_init_requires_router_url(self):\n        \"\"\"Router URL must be provided via arg or ROUTER_URL env.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_init_creates_session_when_not_provided(self):\n        \"\"\"Should create session via ControlPlaneClient.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_init_reuses_provided_session_id(self):\n        \"\"\"Should not create new session when session_id provided.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup(self):\n        \"\"\"Should delete session if data plane init fails after create.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_context_manager_cleanup(self):\n        \"\"\"Should call stop() on context exit.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_execute_command_delegates_to_data_plane(self):\n        \"\"\"Should delegate to CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_run_code_python_path(self):\n        \"\"\"Should write file and execute python3 for python/py/python3.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient Tests\n\n```python\n# test_agent_runtime.py\nclass TestAgentRuntimeClient:\n    def test_bootstrap_session_id_on_init(self):\n        \"\"\"Should GET base URL and extract session header.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises(self):\n        \"\"\"Should raise ValueError if session header missing.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_invoke_without_session_raises(self):\n        \"\"\"Should raise ValueError if session_id is falsy.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_invoke_posts_json_with_headers(self):\n        \"\"\"Should POST JSON with session header.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_context_manager_closes_session(self):\n        \"\"\"Should close HTTP session on context exit.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### ControlPlaneClient Tests\n\n```python\n# test_control_plane.py\nclass TestControlPlaneClient:\n    def test_create_session_posts_json(self):\n        \"\"\"Should POST to /v1/code-interpreter with correct body.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_create_session_returns_session_id(self):\n        \"\"\"Should return sessionId from response.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_create_session_missing_session_id_raises(self):\n        \"\"\"Should raise ValueError if response missing sessionId.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_delete_session_returns_true_on_success(self):\n        \"\"\"Should return True on 2xx.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_delete_session_returns_true_on_404(self):\n        \"\"\"Should return True on 404 (already deleted).\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_delete_session_returns_false_on_error(self):\n        \"\"\"Should return False and log warning on other errors.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_auth_from_service_account_token(self):\n        \"\"\"Should read token from SA file when auth_token not provided.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### Data Plane Client Tests\n\n```python\n# test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py\nclass TestCodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def test_base_url_construction(self):\n        \"\"\"Should construct base URL from router_url + namespace + cr_name.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_execute_command_posts_json(self):\n        \"\"\"Should POST to api/execute with command array and timeout.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_execute_command_timeout_buffer(self):\n        \"\"\"Read timeout should be timeout + 2.0 seconds.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_execute_command_raises_on_nonzero_exit(self):\n        \"\"\"Should raise CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit_code.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_write_file_posts_base64(self):\n        \"\"\"Should POST to api/files with base64 content, path, mode.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_upload_file_multipart(self):\n        \"\"\"Should POST multipart with file, path, mode, session header.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_download_file_streams(self):\n        \"\"\"Should GET with stream=True for file download.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_list_files_gets_with_path_query(self):\n        \"\"\"Should GET api/files with path query param.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### Mock Server Integration Tests\n\n```python\n# Integration test example\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_router():\n    \"\"\"Start mock Router server for testing.\"\"\"\n    # Using responses or httpserver library\n    \ndef test_full_lifecycle(mock_router):\n    \"\"\"Test create session, execute, stop flow.\"\"\"\n    with CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=mock_router.url) as client:\n        result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n        assert result == \"hello\\n\"\n    # Verify session deleted on exit\n```\n\n### E2E Test Script\n\n```python\n# scripts/e2e_picod_test.py\n\"\"\"End-to-end test for PicoD integration.\n\nRequires:\n    - Running Workload Manager\n    - Running Router\n    - Accessible Code Interpreter environment\n\nUsage:\n    python scripts/e2e_picod_test.py\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Required\n\n```toml\n[project]\nname = \"agentcube-sdk\"\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n```\n\n### Package Discovery\n\n```toml\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\nwhere = [\".\"]\ninclude = [\"agentcube*\"]\nnamespaces = false\n```\n\n---\n\n## Public API Surface\n\n### Root Exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n```\n\n### Clients Subpackage (`agentcube/clients/__init__.py`)\n\n```python\n__all__ = [\n    \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n    \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n    \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Session Header Management\n\n- Header name: `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase)\n- Set as default on data plane HTTP session\n- Explicitly set on multipart uploads\n\n### Timeout Handling\n\n- Control plane: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n- Data plane execute: `timeout + 2.0` buffer to prevent race with PicoD\n- Per-call override supported via method `timeout` parameter\n\n### Python Code Execution Path\n\nWhen `run_code()` called with `language` in `(\"python\", \"py\", \"python3\")`:\n\n1. Generate timestamped filename: `{name}_{timestamp}.py`\n2. Write code via `write_file()`\n3. Execute via `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\")`\n\n### Token Authentication\n\n1. If `auth_token` provided, use it\n2. Else try read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n3. If token non-empty, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775902781767,"end":1775902781881}}}}
